
1. South Sudan is the youngest country in the world. It gained independence from Sudan in 
2011 after a bloody civil war.
2.  The civil war has caused a lot of damage to the economy with the value of the countryâ€™s currency 
on a constant decline. Right now the country has the lowest GDP per capita in the world.
3. Most people in the country reside in rural areas and live on less than a dollar a day.
4. In South Sudan, the wealth is measured by the number of cattle that each family owns.
5. South Sudan has the highest illiteracy rate in the world. Only 16% of South Sudanese 
children ever go to school and only 1.9% complete primary school.
